body_html:
@nataliaponomareva @shivaniag Are there any examples that use a multi-label loss for Boosted Trees? As far as I can see, BoostedTreesRegressor is currently only implemented for label_dimension=1. In the constructor, _label_dimension=HOLD_FOR_MULTI_DIM_SUPPORT is a placeholder. I believe multi-dimensional labels are not supported yet. Please correct me if I'm wrong.

body:
@nataliaponomareva @shivaniag  Are there any examples that use a multi-label loss for Boosted Trees? As far as I can see, [BoostedTreesRegressor ](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/tf/estimator/BoostedTreesRegressor) is currently only implemented for _label_dimension=1_. In the [constructor](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/tf/estimator/BoostedTreesRegressor#__init__), _label_dimension=_HOLD_FOR_MULTI_DIM_SUPPORT_ is a placeholder. I believe multi-dimensional labels are not supported yet. Please correct me if I'm wrong.
